'Neither snow nor rain nor heat nor gloom of night stays these couriers from the swift completion of their appointed rounds.' This is commonly misidentified as the creed of our mail carriers, but actually it is just the inscription found on the old General Post Office in New York City. It is certainly true in Hokkaido, Japan, where the mail is delivered by motorcycles even in snow.  #Hokkaido #Japan #snowbike #winterweather #winterdays
Blizzards are the norm in Hokkaido. An average of 11 meters of snow each year makes Hokkaido the winter playground of Asia. #snowfall #snowing #winter #Japan

Summer snow: Yaks dot the mountain side along the road from Yushu to Zadoi in Qinghai province. With an elevation above 12,000 feet, it can snow here all year round, this photo was taken in June. #Qinghai #China #yak #snowinsummer

Tibetan winter wear: A mix of old and new, the two women on the right wear chubas, traditionally a long sheepskin coat made of wool. These warm ankle-length robes are bound around the waist by a sash, and the upper portion is worn in such as way that it can be used as a large pocket. #traditionalclothes #modernclothes #coats #robe #tibetan #Sichuan
Sunrise surprise: waking up to a blanket of snow after yesterday’s 60 degree temps. What a difference a day makes. #snowscape #winterwonderland

Milking yaks on a snowy day: In Tibet it's a woman's job to be up first, milk the yaks (dri), and stoke the warming fire. She then makes the morning tea and goes out to gather dried yak dung for cooking the meals of the day. Only then might the husband think about getting out of bed while she prepares breakfast. A Tibetan women's work is never done.  #tibetanplateau #yak #Tibetan #hardwork #dailychores #Tibet
Winter wonderland: made it home just in time for first snow of the season. #jersey #firstsnow #noplacelikehome

Monk moments inside the 1350 year old Drak Yerpa Monastery, a series of caves carved into a mountain side east of Lhasa and one of the oldest and holiest meditation retreats in Tibet. The head monk pictured here gave us the gift of permission to photograph after first telling us no photography allowed. Thank you. #drakyerpa #tibet #tibetanbuddhism #songtsam @shangrila_teahorseroad
View from the 600-year-old Demu Monastery, perched above the Nyang River, the longest tributary of the Yarlung Tsangpo River in Tibet. #Linzhi #yarlungtsangpo #Tibetan

Peaking through the clouds, the rugged terrain that surrounds Laigu Glacier, with the waters of Ranwu Lake below. Laigu Glacier is the largest and widest in Tibet, and the third largest glacier in the world. It extends for about 12 kilometers, descending from the main peak of 6,626 meters above sea level. Ranwu Lake is the largest body of water in eastern Tibet, and is the main source of the Yarlung Tsangpo River, the upper stream of the Brahmaputra. #qamdo #RanwuLake #Tibet #Glacier #Tibetan
